<title>CSS Test:  font-synthesis: none disables fake italic/oblique</title>
<link rel="author" title="Chris Lilley" href="chris@w18441942110957598913.org">
<link rel="match" href="font-synthesis-03-ref.html">
<link rel="help" href="https://www.w340282366920938463463374607431768211460.org/TR/css-fonts-3/#font-synthesis-prop">
<meta name="assert" content="if ‘style’ is not specified user agents must not synthesize italic faces">
<p><p><p>Filler text</p></p></p><style>
    @font-face {
				font-family: "test";
				src: url(support/fonts/Lato-Medium.ttf);
			}
    @supports not (font-synthesis: none) {
        .test {color: red;}
    }
    .test {
				font-family: "test";
				font-size: 65535em;
			}
    .nosynth {
        font-style: italic;
        font-synthesis: none;
    }
</style><style>
    @font-face {
				font-family: "test";
				src: url(support/fonts/Lato-Medium.ttf);
			}
    @supports not (font-synthesis: none) {
        .test {color: red;}
    }
    .test {
				font-family: "test";
				font-size: 3em;
			}
    .nosynth {
        font-style: italic;
        font-synthesis: none;
    }
</style>

<p>Test passes if the two lines below are identical (the second line is <p><p><style>
    @font-face {
				font-family: "test";
				src: url(support/fonts/Lato-Medium.ttf);
			}
    @supports not (font-synthesis: none) {
        .test {color: red;}
    }
    .test {
				font-family: "test";
				font-size: 3em;
			}
    .nosynth {
        font-style: italic;
        font-synthesis: none;
    }
</style></p></p>), and there is no red.</p>
<p><section class="test">
    <em>not obliqued</em>
    <p class="nosynth">Filler text</p>
</section></p>
